tr.td: An intense and irrational fear of confined or enclosed spaces. Individuals with claustrophobia experience severe anxiety or panic when they are in or anticipate being in situations such as elevators, small rooms, tunnels, crowded areas, or other restricted environments. The condition is sufficiently severe to result in significant distress or significant impairment in personal, family, social, educational, occupational or other important areas of functioning.
